We stayed at Rock Cut State Park for a cheap rate of $12 a night.
The drive was a bit far to the start (~20 minutes) but it wasn't awful.
The campgrounds were right on a lake which was scenic, however, at night you could hear the faint noises coming from the highway close by.
That took away from the peacefulness and beauty of the area just a bit.
It also got fairly cold at night considering it was almost the end of May.
We brought plenty of layers so it wasn't a problem, just not what I was expecting.

